-- Bank Audi to Start Turkish Operations by October, Hurriyet Says
-- B y   S i b e l   A k b a y
-- 2012-08-24T07:49:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-24/bank-audi-to-start-turkish-operations-by-october-hurriyet-says.html
     Aug. 24 (Bloomberg)-- Lebanon’s Bank Audi Sal-Audi Saradar
Group, which will operate in  Turkey  under the name Odea Bank,
will open its first branch in Istanbul by the end of September
or beginning of October,  Hurriyet  newspaper said, citing Freddie C. Baz, Saradar Group’s Chief Financial Officer and Strategy
Director.  Bank Audi, the largest lender in Lebanon by assets, got a
license from Turkey’s banking regulator in October 2011 to set
up a bank in Turkey, becoming the first bank to get a license in
12 years, the Istanbul-based  Hurriyet  reported.  Click here for web link   To contact the reporter on this story:
